Replace country names with 3-letter ISO abbreviations

use_iso_countries.Rd

The IEA uses full country names, but it is more concise to use the 3-letter ISO abbreviations. This function replaces the full country names with ISO abbreviations where possible.

use_iso_countries(
  .iea_df,
  country = "Country",
  iea_china_HK = "People's Republic of China",
  ieatools_china = "CHN"
)

Arguments

.iea_df

A data frame containing a country column
country

The name of the country column in .iea_df. Default is "Country".
iea_china_HK

The IEA string for China and Hong Kong. Default is "China (P.R. of China and Hong Kong, China)".
ieatools_china

The 3-letter string that replaces iea_china_HK. Default is "CHN".

Value

.iea_df with 3-letter ISO country abbreviations in the country column.

Details

Special cases are considered where IEA extended energy balance data country names differ from countrycode package country names.

IEA namecountrycode name (names)use_iso_countries() decision
"People's Republic of China""China""CHN"

Examples

sample_iea_data_path() %>% 
  iea_df() %>%
  rename_iea_df_cols() %>% 
  use_iso_countries()
